ct, but I'll eat my dog food and try to improve it. I replaced markdown-mode with my immature mode and started to use it daily life.</p><p>Feel free to send me any types of feedback suck as opening new issue, sending pull request, mentioning on twitter, etc.</p>" "http://blog.kyanny.me/entry/2013/01/14/180534" (20723 51806) new 4 nil nil ((title nil "markdown-highlight-mode.el") (link ((href . "http://blog.kyanny.me/entry/2013/01/14/180534"))) (id nil "http://blog.kyanny.me/id/12704914408862975456") (published nil "2013-01-14T18:05:34+09:00") (updated nil "2013-01-14T18:05:34+09:00") (summary nil "UPDATE id:syohex told me that the forked version of markdown-mode is hosted on github and fixed some bugs including weird behaviour of dabbr") (content ((type . "html")) "<p><strong>UPDATE</strong><br />
